Dishcloths...

02:14.082 --> 02:16.249
silverware...

02:16.351 --> 02:18.051
plates...

02:18.153 --> 02:19.616
cereal.

02:20.522 --> 02:24.391
Dishcloths... silverware...
plates... cereal.

02:24.459 --> 02:27.193
Dishcloths, silverware, plates, cereal.

02:27.295 --> 02:30.830
♪

03:13.408 --> 03:16.309
<i>My name is Adam Warren.</i>

03:16.378 --> 03:18.678
<i>And I came back.</i>

03:24.619 --> 03:27.053
<i>But I didn't come home.</i>

03:27.155 --> 03:33.337
Synced & corrected by -robtor-
www.addic7ed.com

03:37.399 --> 03:39.132
Claire: Hey, mister. Slow down.

03:39.234 --> 03:40.366
Danny: I'm hungry.

03:40.469 --> 03:42.902
But you need to come up for air, too.

03:43.004 --> 03:44.337
- Wow.
- Cute, huh?

03:44.439 --> 03:46.673
Well, if by "cute," you
mean "vaguely upsetting."

03:46.775 --> 03:49.109
- [Gasps, chuckles]
- Do I have to go to this thing today?

03:49.211 --> 03:50.410
You're going, mister.

03:50.512 --> 03:51.678
Oh, no, it's no big deal, John.

03:51.780 --> 03:52.879
If the kids want to
do their own thing...

03:52.981 --> 03:54.814
Honey, you spent the
best years of your life

03:54.883 --> 03:56.049
making us demonic bananas.

03:56.118 --> 03:56.987
[Chuckles]

03:57.089 --> 03:59.486
The least we could do is get
you elected to City Council.

03:59.588 --> 04:00.587
[Chuckles]

04:00.689 --> 04:02.634
It's your dream. Let's
make it happen, huh?

04:02.702 --> 04:04.100
Oh.

04:04.263 --> 04:06.259
Oh, Adam, you'll miss the bus again.

04:08.296 --> 04:10.864
Lunch! Bye, sweetie.

04:10.932 --> 04:12.443
Have a good day. [Smooches]

04:12.545 --> 04:14.167
Bye.

04:14.269 --> 04:15.768
How does he keep missing it?

04:15.871 --> 04:17.137
The stop's right there.

04:17.238 --> 04:18.171
[Door closes]

04:18.273 --> 04:19.873
Hank: Here's where you went wrong.

04:19.975 --> 04:21.241
Adam: What?

04:21.343 --> 04:24.244
Too much glue on the stay.

04:24.346 --> 04:27.680
That's why your mast is jammed.

04:27.782 --> 04:29.782
[Thunder rumbles]

04:29.885 --> 04:31.284
[Chuckles]

04:32.483 --> 04:33.849
You'll get it.

04:33.951 --> 04:35.582
All right, you better go.

04:36.274 --> 04:37.540
Okay.

04:42.519 --> 04:44.786
Are you coming to the rally later?

04:46.382 --> 04:47.347
I don't know.

04:47.450 --> 04:49.144
They're gonna have cotton candy.

04:49.885 --> 04:51.203
[Brakes squeal]

04:51.305 --> 04:52.686
Better go.

04:52.788 --> 04:54.296
You'll miss your bus again.

04:54.398 --> 04:55.589
Bye, Hank.

04:55.691 --> 04:57.457
Bye, Adam.

04:58.527 --> 05:01.395
[Thunder rumbles]

05:06.869 --> 05:09.736
[Bus departs]

05:11.373 --> 05:15.175
[Thunder crashes]

05:15.277 --> 05:17.611
[Sighs]

05:20.787 --> 05:22.015
Is Adam up?

05:22.117 --> 05:24.885
Why? Do you need him for
another press conference?

05:24.987 --> 05:26.487
I was going to tell you.

05:26.589 --> 05:29.434
Well, before or after you moved
into the governor's mansion?

05:29.459 --> 05:31.325
I was going to tell you I was running

05:31.427 --> 05:33.293
the night before I announced,
but you weren't home.

05:33.395 --> 05:34.461
I didn't have a chance.

05:38.882 --> 05:40.634
No, that's for Adam.

05:40.736 --> 05:41.871
All of it?

05:41.973 --> 05:44.071
He never got treats down there.

05:44.173 --> 05:46.473
No one's ever gonna squeeze <i>
him</i> into a hole again.

05:46.575 --> 05:49.576
He's been through a
lot, so let's just try

05:49.678 --> 05:53.881
and make things as routine
and normal for him as we can.

05:54.783 --> 05:56.750
Sure thing.

05:58.354 --> 05:59.920
Cops are here.

06:01.386 --> 06:03.323
Nina: We've got officers
on both ends of the street.

06:03.425 --> 06:04.858
Nobody's getting near the
house without us knowing.

06:04.960 --> 06:05.926
What about the press?

06:06.028 --> 06:06.930
They're pushed behind the perimeter.

06:07.032 --> 06:08.756
- You can relax.
- Sure, we'll kick back.

06:08.858 --> 06:10.190
So, why isn't he in custody yet?

06:10.292 --> 06:11.999
- We're working on that.
- And what if you're wrong?

06:12.101 --> 06:13.400
We've been here before.

06:13.469 --> 06:14.578
- Claire.
- I want the guy caught!

06:14.680 --> 06:15.711
So do I.

06:15.813 --> 06:17.175
What are you gonna do to him?

06:18.683 --> 06:20.386
When you catch him.

06:21.377 --> 06:25.279
♪

06:25.347 --> 06:26.761
Are you gonna hurt him?

06:28.384 --> 06:31.618
Oh, no, don't you worry.

06:31.720 --> 06:35.222
We're gonna keep you safe from now on.

06:35.324 --> 06:37.257
You're gonna be fine.

06:37.326 --> 06:40.309
Everything's gonna go
back to normal, okay?

06:42.298 --> 06:45.232
Okay. [Sighs]

06:45.334 --> 06:49.303
♪

06:49.405 --> 06:51.405
The kid was in a basement for 10 years.

06:51.540 --> 06:53.440
Is his brain mashed potatoes or what?

06:53.542 --> 06:55.108
This is a human-interest story.

06:55.210 --> 06:56.510
One of you please make me cry.

06:56.612 --> 06:57.678
The rest of you,

06:57.746 --> 06:59.780
work the governor's
side, Warren's platform.

06:59.882 --> 07:01.915
Every inch of this
thing needs to be probed.

07:02.017 --> 07:03.250
All right.

07:03.352 --> 07:04.585
Danish?

07:04.687 --> 07:06.753
Oh, don't Danish me until
you find that DNA doctor.

07:06.855 --> 07:09.089
The hospital outsourced
the test to a genetics lab.

07:09.191 --> 07:11.525
- So he <i> does</i> exist.
- Not exactly.

07:12.296 --> 07:14.061
He threw himself in front of a train

07:14.163 --> 07:15.829
two days after verifying the kid's DNA.

07:15.931 --> 07:18.065
- It's a coincidence.
- Convenient.

07:19.101 --> 07:21.735
Gonna need more.

07:23.172 --> 07:24.905
Claire: Take him to the mall.

07:25.007 --> 07:26.985
The Farmington one. It
should be quiet there.

07:27.087 --> 07:28.838
There won't be any press.

07:28.940 --> 07:30.277
And, um...

07:31.067 --> 07:33.780
buy him some new shoes,
take him to lunch.

07:33.882 --> 07:35.282
- Maybe catch a movie.
- A movie?

07:35.384 --> 07:37.081
A little fun wouldn't hurt.

07:38.554 --> 07:40.487
Bye. Bye.

07:40.589 --> 07:43.957
I'll see you later.

07:44.059 --> 07:46.059
Have fun. Okay?

07:46.161 --> 07:47.127
Got it?

07:47.229 --> 07:48.929
- Movie.
- Movie.

07:49.031 --> 07:50.797
Movies cost money.

07:50.899 --> 07:52.232
Okay, I got it.

07:52.334 --> 07:54.835
You got the taillight fixed, Danny.

07:54.937 --> 07:56.436
[Door closes]

07:56.538 --> 07:58.451
Yeah, only took him three years.

07:59.808 --> 08:02.009
I need to get gas, too.

08:02.111 --> 08:03.377
[Door opens]

08:03.479 --> 08:04.444
Hang on.

08:04.546 --> 08:06.413
She wants me to take him to a movie.

08:07.650 --> 08:09.216
[Birds chirping]

08:09.318 --> 08:12.352
[Door creaks]

08:17.126 --> 08:20.227
[Sighs]

08:22.364 --> 08:24.817
[Chuckles]

08:24.961 --> 08:26.261
Hi.

08:28.071 --> 08:29.216
Hi.

08:33.124 --> 08:34.657
Remember me?

08:37.546 --> 08:39.479
I'm the guy that killed you.

08:39.581 --> 08:42.049
John: Adam?!

08:42.150 --> 08:44.685
Get in the car, okay?

08:44.787 --> 08:46.072
Come on.

08:47.489 --> 08:51.925
♪

09:26.792 --> 09:28.192
Hi. Hi, there! Hi. Hi, there.

09:28.294 --> 09:29.193
Um, I'm Claire Warren,

09:29.295 --> 09:30.561
and I'm running for City Council.

09:30.663 --> 09:31.562
Have a nice day.

09:31.664 --> 09:34.698
♪

09:49.938 --> 09:50.977
Hi!

09:51.071 --> 09:52.041
You came.

09:57.318 --> 09:59.651
Nina: You didn't see him
talking to any strangers?

09:59.753 --> 10:02.122
Just me, the ice-cream guy, and Hank.

10:02.224 --> 10:03.126
[Gasps]

10:03.151 --> 10:04.539
Who's hank, Willa?

10:04.726 --> 10:05.692
Just our neighbor.

10:05.794 --> 10:07.126
John: Years ago, there was some sort

10:07.228 --> 10:09.090
of an indecent-exposure
thing in a park.

10:09.192 --> 10:10.763
"Thing"?! Try conviction!

10:10.865 --> 10:13.232
- The man is a sex offender.
- [Knock on door]

10:14.442 --> 10:15.668
Hank Asher?

10:17.182 --> 10:17.999
Can I help you?

10:18.102 --> 10:19.972
Hi, I'm Officer Meyer.

10:20.041 --> 10:21.507
Do you know Adam Warren?

10:22.884 --> 10:24.116
Lives across the street.

10:24.206 --> 10:25.839
Is everything okay?

10:26.114 --> 10:28.181
Adam disappeared a couple hours ago.

10:28.316 --> 10:30.626
Were you at the rally in the park?

10:32.587 --> 10:34.452
Simple question... yes or no.

10:34.554 --> 10:36.923
Hank was home with me all night.

10:37.025 --> 10:39.692
Uh, we watch old movies together
on Friday.

10:41.789 --> 10:43.422
Oh. Okay.

10:44.058 --> 10:45.798
Well, thanks for your time.

10:45.900 --> 10:46.999
Thanks.

10:47.102 --> 10:48.501
Which one?

10:49.695 --> 10:50.594
What?

10:50.689 --> 10:51.435
I love them, too.

10:51.498 --> 10:52.864
The classics.

10:52.966 --> 10:54.666
Which one was on?

10:55.620 --> 10:56.868
Goodnight, Officer.

10:56.970 --> 10:59.170
♪

11:00.707 --> 11:03.808
Okay, what we're looking at
is our east quadrant.

11:03.877 --> 11:06.344
It's directly north of our red dragon.

11:06.446 --> 11:07.512
Thanks.

11:07.614 --> 11:09.314
Deep woods, thick brush.

11:09.382 --> 11:11.382
You see anything interesting...

11:11.485 --> 11:13.351
Sanchez: Hobbit, leprechaun?

11:13.453 --> 11:14.452
[Snickers]

11:14.554 --> 11:17.822
Got something to say, Detective?

11:19.359 --> 11:21.960
Anyone else?

11:22.062 --> 11:23.394
Hmm?

11:23.497 --> 11:25.864
I want hourly updates.

11:25.966 --> 11:28.648
Man: You heard the detective.

11:28.755 --> 11:29.787
Let's go.

11:30.136 --> 11:32.504
[Police radio chatter]

11:36.309 --> 11:37.408
What's going on?

11:38.385 --> 11:39.978
Some sicko had a lair in the woods.

11:40.080 --> 11:42.134
They think
he had the mayor's kid in there.

11:42.762 --> 11:44.195
People are animals.

11:55.428 --> 11:58.463
♪

12:04.104 --> 12:06.237
So, you remember my car, huh?

12:07.274 --> 12:09.941
Do you still play football?

12:10.043 --> 12:12.477
You used to really good.

12:13.847 --> 12:15.805
What kind of sleeper are you, Hank?

12:15.830 --> 12:17.482
Side, back, tummy?

12:17.551 --> 12:18.516
I don't sleep.

12:18.618 --> 12:19.817
Insomniac.

12:19.920 --> 12:22.287
You know what's keeping you up at night?

12:22.389 --> 12:24.022
I have a pretty good idea.

12:24.124 --> 12:25.857
Bad mattress.

12:25.959 --> 12:27.425
Does it have a box spring?

12:27.527 --> 12:29.928
- No.
- Is the padding foam?

12:30.030 --> 12:32.163
It's a prison mattress.

12:33.133 --> 12:33.703
[Chuckles]

12:33.805 --> 12:35.567
Bottom line, you're looking for comfort.

12:35.669 --> 12:37.235
Got great bang for your buck here.

12:38.060 --> 12:39.470
What else do you remember?

12:39.573 --> 12:40.738
- About what?
- Anything.

12:40.840 --> 12:42.974
I mean, you remember
what school you went to?

12:43.609 --> 12:46.945
Or what do you...
what do you remember about Alex?

12:47.981 --> 12:49.714
I don't remember him.

12:49.816 --> 12:50.882
Her.

12:50.984 --> 12:53.151
♪

12:53.253 --> 12:55.353
She was your best friend.

12:57.657 --> 12:59.857
Memory foam, inner spring,
retails for about $500,

12:59.960 --> 13:02.093
but with the special
we got going, you could...

13:02.162 --> 13:03.261
What about that one?

13:03.363 --> 13:04.462
The Imperial.

13:04.564 --> 13:06.664
French lamb's wool
sewn inside Texas cotton.

13:06.766 --> 13:08.132
It's a little pricier
than the other options.

13:08.234 --> 13:09.133
How much?

13:09.235 --> 13:11.369
$10,000.

13:11.471 --> 13:14.372
[Sighs]

13:16.409 --> 13:18.370
I've been saving up.

13:18.812 --> 13:20.411
♪

13:20.513 --> 13:22.411
So, you want to try something on?

13:22.949 --> 13:24.749
I wore these.

13:24.851 --> 13:26.351
[Scoffs]

13:26.453 --> 13:28.135
Kind of old-school, huh?

13:28.360 --> 13:29.211
No.

13:29.442 --> 13:32.190
I wore ones just like these
when he took me.

13:32.292 --> 13:36.995
♪

13:38.598 --> 13:40.598
My brother comes home
after 10 years of torture,

13:40.700 --> 13:42.033
I'm calling in sick for at least a week.

13:42.135 --> 13:43.201
You're a douche.

13:43.303 --> 13:45.370
So you suspect, but don't want
to confirm socially.

13:45.472 --> 13:46.537
Say with a drink?

13:46.606 --> 13:47.872
I don't drink, Ryan, or date.

13:47.974 --> 13:48.873
Men?

13:48.975 --> 13:50.375
People. Poll numbers?

13:50.477 --> 13:52.777
Well, thanks to the 24-hour news cycle,

13:52.879 --> 13:54.278
name recognition's off the charts,

13:54.381 --> 13:56.042
and the association
is overwhelmingly positive.

13:56.067 --> 13:56.571
But?

13:56.650 --> 13:58.845
People are questioning if she can
handle the business of being governor.

13:58.948 --> 14:01.619
You know, given everything
you guys are going through.

14:01.721 --> 14:04.222
Book us one of those
big sit-down interviews

14:04.324 --> 14:05.490
for the whole family.

14:05.592 --> 14:06.824
Let them see that we're healing.

14:06.926 --> 14:08.126
Are you?

14:08.228 --> 14:09.127
What?

14:09.229 --> 14:10.628
Healing.

14:11.436 --> 14:13.131
We will be.

14:16.469 --> 14:20.038
[Floorboard creaks]

14:20.140 --> 14:23.975
[Door opens, closes]

14:26.079 --> 14:33.317
♪

14:42.629 --> 14:44.729
Adam?

14:44.831 --> 14:46.798
Adam: Mom?

14:46.900 --> 14:49.934
♪

15:03.917 --> 15:08.453
[Door creaks]

15:09.923 --> 15:13.224
Hi.

15:15.261 --> 15:17.161
What are you doing in here?

15:17.263 --> 15:19.597
Sleeping.

15:21.134 --> 15:23.735
Why aren't you in your bed?

15:24.771 --> 15:28.606
I can't sleep in there.

15:30.276 --> 15:32.543
Adam.

15:34.581 --> 15:36.778
I need to touch the walls.

15:37.717 --> 15:44.822
♪

15:52.201 --> 15:53.133
[Sighs]

15:54.132 --> 15:55.865
He's sleeping on the closet floor

15:55.967 --> 15:58.568
because he would rather
be in a cage than...

15:58.670 --> 15:59.736
He needs time.

15:59.804 --> 16:01.938
- Well, how much?
- I don't know.

16:02.040 --> 16:04.340
A... a... and he's also concerned
about how we're gonna treat

16:04.442 --> 16:05.675
the man that tortured him.

16:05.777 --> 16:07.744
It's all very normal.
Given the circumstances.

16:07.846 --> 16:08.396
[Sighs]

16:08.421 --> 16:10.471
Your son was 8 years
old when he was taken.

16:10.549 --> 16:11.814
I know. We have done the math.
Thank you.

16:11.916 --> 16:13.583
So Adam spent more time
with his kidnapper

16:13.685 --> 16:15.799
- than he ever did at home.
- No.

16:15.867 --> 16:18.659
For all practical purposes,
this guy was Adam's family.

16:18.761 --> 16:20.089
- No!
- I know that this is hard to hear...

16:20.191 --> 16:20.991
I... I know. No.

16:21.016 --> 16:22.049
...but you've got to wrap
your head around...

16:22.127 --> 16:23.459
You are his doctor, all right?

16:23.561 --> 16:25.028
You are supposed to be fixing him.

16:25.130 --> 16:27.230
He's not a broken toilet, he's our son.

16:27.298 --> 16:28.564
No, no, he's not.

16:28.666 --> 16:30.666
He's not our son. He's just...

16:30.735 --> 16:33.669
♪

16:34.706 --> 16:36.839
Claire: He's...

16:36.941 --> 16:38.341
[Sighs]

16:38.443 --> 16:42.045
He is in there somewhere.

16:42.147 --> 16:45.389
Please, just help us find him.

16:45.990 --> 16:47.523
[Sighs]

16:49.387 --> 16:52.476
Chief. Why can't you just
give me one more day?

16:52.591 --> 16:54.190
You know what, one has a nasty habit

16:54.292 --> 16:56.095
of turning into a lot more
than one, so no, I can't.

16:56.242 --> 16:57.508
We just have 30 acres left.

16:57.610 --> 16:58.876
If you just give me like five guys,

16:58.978 --> 16:59.810
maybe even three, we can...

16:59.835 --> 17:01.178
Look, even the child's psych

17:01.280 --> 17:02.780
says that this red dragon
is probably a...

17:02.882 --> 17:04.147
what's it... a-a mental construct.

17:04.250 --> 17:06.550
His imagination
protecting him from trauma.

17:08.521 --> 17:10.020
I can't have my guys
wandering around in the woods

17:10.123 --> 17:11.756
when I need them to re-interview

17:11.858 --> 17:12.843
all the vendors
from the rally that night.

17:12.867 --> 17:13.748
We did that 10 years ago.

17:13.826 --> 17:16.527
Not to mention
75,000 people live in the city,

17:16.628 --> 17:19.896
and when they call 911,
they want someone to answer.

17:19.999 --> 17:22.165
There's nothing there, Meyer.

17:22.268 --> 17:24.101
I'm calling it.

17:25.137 --> 17:29.507
But tell him we're doing
everything we can.

17:32.378 --> 17:35.230
John: He's sleeping in his closet now

17:36.349 --> 17:39.116
so that he can touch the walls
during the night

17:39.218 --> 17:43.287
'cause a tiny, dark closet
feels more like home to him

17:43.389 --> 17:44.345
than his <i> actual</i> home.

17:44.447 --> 17:46.857
Chief doesn't believe what we're
looking for is in those woods.

17:46.959 --> 17:48.777
- Do you?
- John...

17:48.879 --> 17:49.593
Come on, do you?

17:49.695 --> 17:53.297
♪

17:53.399 --> 17:54.999
[Sighs]

17:55.067 --> 17:57.301
We're not stopping the search.

17:57.370 --> 17:59.436
We're just refocusing elsewhere.

17:59.539 --> 18:02.096
While he gets further and further away.

18:08.581 --> 18:12.116
I keep having this dream
that I'm killing people.

18:12.218 --> 18:14.385
Innocent people.

18:15.354 --> 18:17.254
My fingers around their necks,

18:17.356 --> 18:19.657
pushing sharp things into their guts,

18:19.759 --> 18:22.126
making them bleed, one after the other.

18:22.228 --> 18:23.594
You want to kill him.

18:23.696 --> 18:25.396
It's... It's understandable.

18:25.498 --> 18:28.432
No, I want to kill everyone he loves.

18:28.534 --> 18:31.902
♪

19:09.575 --> 19:12.009
Much better than
the silly kid stuff, right?

19:12.111 --> 19:14.144
You could put up some more posters,

19:14.247 --> 19:17.147
maybe get a flat screen.
That could be cool.

19:17.250 --> 19:19.416
And we could get you a new bedspread.

19:19.518 --> 19:21.452
We can look for colors tomorrow.

19:21.554 --> 19:23.087
And if you feel like it,

19:23.189 --> 19:25.522
you can try on some of those new shirts.

19:25.625 --> 19:27.391
Okay.

19:27.493 --> 19:28.699
Okay.

19:32.465 --> 19:34.064
Uh, you want to brush your teeth?

19:34.788 --> 19:36.795
Yeah, sure.

19:43.476 --> 19:45.643
Oh, could you get the pillow
from the guest room?

19:45.711 --> 19:47.144
I think it's a little softer
than this one.

19:47.246 --> 19:49.146
And we'll go over
the options for the interview.

19:49.248 --> 19:50.147
Mom...

19:50.249 --> 19:51.548
Get the pillow... now.

19:59.091 --> 20:04.595
♪

20:54.046 --> 20:55.746
This is Detective Meyer. Come in.

20:55.848 --> 20:57.514
Dispatcher: Go ahead, Detective.

20:57.616 --> 21:00.617
I need backup at the 18th mile
of Franklin Woods Road.

21:00.720 --> 21:02.286
Uh, I think I found something.

21:02.388 --> 21:03.821
A... a door, a metal door.

21:03.923 --> 21:05.756
It's the... it's the
Adam Warren investigation.

21:05.858 --> 21:06.824
Stand by.

21:06.926 --> 21:09.660
I've got officers on the way, Detective.

21:09.762 --> 21:11.762
[Explosion]

21:11.864 --> 21:12.963
11-71!

21:13.065 --> 21:14.631
I need backup and the fire department!

21:14.734 --> 21:16.800
He's burning the evidence!
He's burning it all down!

21:16.902 --> 21:19.303
The suspect is here
and he's burning it down!

21:21.451 --> 21:23.608
I bought these for the Warrens.

21:23.710 --> 21:26.814
Uh, take the wrappers off
and... and run them over.

21:28.468 --> 21:30.435
- Mom...
- That poor family.

21:30.537 --> 21:33.738
I can't imagine
what they're going through.

21:33.807 --> 21:36.341
I don't think that's a very good idea.

21:39.980 --> 21:42.313
Go and make things right.

21:42.416 --> 21:45.850
We both know you didn't hurt that boy.

21:55.295 --> 21:57.128
Hello. [Clears throat]

21:57.230 --> 21:59.130
These are some muffins.

22:05.948 --> 22:08.820
I'm very sorry
for what you're going through.

22:14.697 --> 22:16.355
Exactly what was the nature

22:16.457 --> 22:18.385
of your relationship with my son?

22:24.391 --> 22:25.985
He was nice to me.

22:28.628 --> 22:30.068
He was a good boy.

22:30.697 --> 22:33.431
[Whimpers]

22:33.533 --> 22:35.500
Mrs. Warren?

22:37.537 --> 22:39.471
[Whispering] Is. Is.

22:41.087 --> 22:42.005
What? I'm sorry.

22:42.058 --> 22:42.874
[Normal voice] Is! Is!

22:42.976 --> 22:45.076
He <i> is</i> a good boy!

22:45.178 --> 22:49.380
♪

23:06.399 --> 23:09.434
[Indistinct conversations]

23:10.871 --> 23:13.905
[ <i> Rock music playing</i> ]

23:17.611 --> 23:20.145
Starting without me?

23:20.247 --> 23:21.179
[Chuckles]

23:21.281 --> 23:22.680
For real, you are like a stalker.

23:22.782 --> 23:24.015
<i>You</i> made me into one.

23:24.117 --> 23:26.017
Whoa, I... I was going to call.

23:26.119 --> 23:27.785
Oh, what? You lost my number?

23:27.888 --> 23:28.786
- No.
- Mm.

23:28.889 --> 23:30.421
No. I, um...

23:30.524 --> 23:33.358
I washed my jeans.

23:35.896 --> 23:37.169
Who writes stuff on a napkin?

23:37.271 --> 23:38.102
I...

23:38.204 --> 23:40.673
- Bam!
- Oh. Oh, man.

23:40.775 --> 23:41.604
Okay.

23:41.629 --> 23:44.802
So, when you're not stalking
dudes from high school...

23:44.905 --> 23:46.037
[Chuckling] Okay.

23:46.139 --> 23:47.438
... what do you do?

23:47.541 --> 23:48.606
Oh.

23:48.708 --> 23:50.572
I was really hoping
you wouldn't ask that.

23:50.674 --> 23:52.120
Are you a rocket scientist?

23:52.222 --> 23:53.190
[Laughs]

23:53.215 --> 23:55.066
All right, you ready for this jelly?

23:55.168 --> 23:57.080
Oh, yeah. I am ready for the jelly.

23:57.182 --> 23:58.745
[Laughs]

23:58.867 --> 24:01.791
Senior Executive Director
of Photocopying at Kinkos.

24:01.893 --> 24:03.470
- Mm-hmm.
- Mnh-mnh.

24:03.572 --> 24:04.838
I'm huge in neighborhood printing.

24:04.940 --> 24:05.839
Wow.

24:05.941 --> 24:07.073
That <i> is</i> intimidating.

24:07.175 --> 24:08.675
I'm leaning in.

24:08.777 --> 24:11.743
- [Chuckling] You should.
- [Both laugh]

24:11.845 --> 24:12.979
So, do you want another round?

24:13.081 --> 24:16.483
I do, but... I won't

24:16.585 --> 24:20.571
'cause I'm kind of trying
not to be that sad alcoholic guy

24:20.634 --> 24:22.367
who still lives with his parents.

24:22.470 --> 24:23.108
Yeah.

24:23.210 --> 24:25.268
Yeah, you're super attracted
to me right now, are you?

24:25.370 --> 24:27.940
- You're killing it.
- [Chuckles]

24:28.042 --> 24:30.943
Well, on that note,
I am gonna go take a...

24:31.286 --> 24:32.799
- I'm gonna go use the restroom.
- Mm.

24:32.879 --> 24:35.048
And then I will
chivalrously walk you home

24:35.150 --> 24:37.016
and kiss you goodnight.

24:37.119 --> 24:38.284
[Chuckles] You're killing it.

24:38.353 --> 24:40.317
- Killing it. Oh.
- Careful.

24:40.419 --> 24:42.326
You get the... killing it.

24:42.607 --> 24:43.873
Woman: Here you go.

24:43.975 --> 24:45.715
Oh, we're not gonna need that.

24:45.818 --> 24:46.973
And can you bring us another round?

24:46.998 --> 24:49.459
- Okay.
- Make his a double.

24:52.016 --> 24:55.518
[ <i> Rock music playing</i> ]

24:56.921 --> 24:59.922
[Rattling]

25:03.394 --> 25:04.834
Do you hear that?

25:07.031 --> 25:08.920
What is that?

25:20.598 --> 25:22.832
Claire, what did you do?

25:22.954 --> 25:25.354
[Sniffles, cries]

25:25.516 --> 25:26.347
Oh.

25:27.232 --> 25:30.566
[Sobs]

25:35.936 --> 25:38.795
That's o... It's okay, bud.

25:38.897 --> 25:40.997
All right.

25:43.314 --> 25:45.314
[Sighs]

25:55.213 --> 25:58.036
♪

25:58.109 --> 25:59.590
[Knock on door]

26:04.575 --> 26:06.030
Why did you confess?

26:07.135 --> 26:08.601
See what time it is?

26:08.626 --> 26:10.979
Why did you confess
to a crime you didn't commit?

26:12.339 --> 26:13.863
[Sighs]

26:14.479 --> 26:15.670
You know why.

26:15.772 --> 26:18.067
I want to hear you say it.

26:21.466 --> 26:23.411
They had stuff on me.

26:25.001 --> 26:25.876
They threatened me.

26:25.901 --> 26:28.611
- Oh, so <i> you're</i> the victim here?
- I am a victim.

26:28.713 --> 26:29.527
I'm innocent.

26:29.552 --> 26:30.935
No, you're <i> not</i> innocent.

26:31.916 --> 26:34.363
We stopped looking
because you said you killed him.

26:34.465 --> 26:37.887
And that money they gave you...
that doesn't make you a victim.

26:37.989 --> 26:40.256
It makes you a liar,
it makes you a coward,

26:40.358 --> 26:43.025
and it makes you as sick
as the bastard who did it.

26:43.127 --> 26:45.161
I didn't lock the boy in a basement.

26:45.230 --> 26:46.195
No.

26:46.297 --> 26:48.427
You just made sure that he stayed there.

26:49.300 --> 26:53.703
♪

27:05.350 --> 27:09.385
[Police radio chatter]

27:09.487 --> 27:13.656
♪

27:13.758 --> 27:16.058
[Radio chatter continues]

27:16.160 --> 27:19.295
♪

27:45.058 --> 27:47.039
Nina: <i> What was the dragon doing, Adam?</i>

27:47.064 --> 27:48.315
Adam: <i> The man lied on top of me.</i>

27:48.393 --> 27:49.358
<i>Where was the door?</i>

27:49.460 --> 27:50.609
<i>It was up on the ceiling.</i>

27:50.711 --> 27:51.566
<i>The red dragon...</i>

27:51.591 --> 27:53.474
<i>[Echoing] His skin looks like gravel.</i>

27:53.576 --> 27:56.036
<i>[Echoing] What was
the dragon doing, Adam?</i>

27:56.200 --> 27:57.199
<i>Where was the door?</i>

27:57.322 --> 27:59.522
<i>It was up on the ceiling.</i>

27:59.971 --> 28:04.206
♪

28:16.788 --> 28:20.122
Len: You all right down there, Meyer?

28:21.426 --> 28:25.127
♪

28:25.698 --> 28:26.997
What do you see?

28:28.099 --> 28:30.166
Chief, move to your left.

28:30.268 --> 28:33.703
♪

28:36.480 --> 28:39.474
John: [Echoing] <i>He's
sleeping in his closet now</i>

28:39.790 --> 28:42.458
<i>so that he can touch the
walls during the night</i>

28:43.707 --> 28:48.510
♪

28:50.526 --> 28:52.893
Claire: Our son Adam was...

28:52.962 --> 28:56.717
last seen during candidates night

28:56.904 --> 28:58.337
at Mooreland Park.

28:58.439 --> 29:00.631
He was wearing gray pants

29:00.734 --> 29:04.077
and a white "Claire Warren
for City Council" T-shirt.

29:05.820 --> 29:07.729
If you have any information...

29:09.050 --> 29:11.484
about where Adam is,

29:11.586 --> 29:16.743
or if you remember anything out
of the ordinary from that night,

29:16.845 --> 29:21.227
please contact the Red Pines police.

29:22.764 --> 29:27.667
[Crying] Please, if you
have our boy, please, please.

29:27.776 --> 29:31.862
He's only 8 years old, and
he's never been away from home,

29:31.957 --> 29:33.873
not even for one night.

29:33.975 --> 29:37.343
And he gets scared of the dark.

29:44.715 --> 29:46.853
What did you do with my son?

29:46.955 --> 29:49.088
[Crowd murmuring]

29:49.190 --> 29:51.090
What did you do with my son?

29:51.192 --> 29:54.394
- [Murmuring continues]
- What did you do?

29:54.496 --> 29:56.262
What did you do with my son?

29:56.364 --> 29:58.298
What did you do?! Tell me!

29:58.366 --> 30:01.200
What did you do with my son?

30:01.303 --> 30:02.569
What did you do with my son?

30:02.704 --> 30:03.770
John: Stop! Stop!

30:03.872 --> 30:05.004
Tell me where he is right now!

30:05.106 --> 30:06.372
- You give him to me!
- Stop, stop!

30:06.474 --> 30:08.041
- Tell me!
- Stop! Stop!

30:08.143 --> 30:10.193
- You tell me where he is right now!
- Stop! Stop! Stop!

30:10.295 --> 30:12.111
- You give me back my son!
- Stop! Stop! Stop!

30:12.213 --> 30:15.148
Give me my son! My son!

30:15.250 --> 30:18.051
[Crowd murmuring]

30:18.119 --> 30:19.719
[Sobs]

30:21.022 --> 30:24.691
♪

31:02.631 --> 31:04.797
How many cups is that?

31:04.899 --> 31:06.470
Two. Four.

31:06.573 --> 31:07.200
[Chuckles]

31:07.335 --> 31:11.241
So, I've been fielding initial
offers for the sit-down.

31:11.343 --> 31:12.987
I think we go traditional.

31:13.056 --> 31:16.046
A woman, someone maternal
who you can make cry...

31:16.109 --> 31:17.142
Diane, Meredith.

31:17.399 --> 31:19.879
We need to influence
public perception with this.

31:20.849 --> 31:23.983
We'll obviously need the whole family.

31:25.003 --> 31:26.626
That might be a problem.

31:26.728 --> 31:29.055
Adam? Or Dad?

31:32.861 --> 31:35.261
You'll get him onboard, honey.

31:35.363 --> 31:37.730
You always say just the right thing.

31:44.739 --> 31:47.558
Print the bunker door
and the ladder first.

31:47.660 --> 31:49.725
I don't believe he'd pour
accelerant on his escape route.

31:49.827 --> 31:51.464
So, when we finally get this bastard...

31:51.600 --> 31:53.637
and that's a when, not an if...

31:54.053 --> 31:56.482
any defense attorney worth half
a damn's gonna tear you apart.

31:56.584 --> 31:58.151
What are you talking about?

31:58.762 --> 32:02.116
You worked this case as a
uniformed officer 10 years ago,

32:02.183 --> 32:03.549
Detective Meyer, didn't you?

32:03.651 --> 32:05.918
In fact, didn't you actually
put away someone else

32:06.020 --> 32:07.052
for this crime?

32:09.090 --> 32:10.756
What did you do, Len?

32:10.825 --> 32:12.518
So, given that you arrested a man

32:12.543 --> 32:13.605
who turned out to be innocent,

32:13.630 --> 32:16.851
why should this jury believe
you have the right man now?

32:16.876 --> 32:18.564
What did you do?

32:18.632 --> 32:20.243
For the good of this case, I had to.

32:21.168 --> 32:22.756
Believe me, I didn't want to.

32:23.304 --> 32:26.839
[Camera shutter clicks]

32:26.941 --> 32:30.476
♪

32:38.519 --> 32:42.888
[Indistinct conversation]

32:42.990 --> 32:45.991
♪

32:52.213 --> 32:54.213
[Sighs]

32:57.618 --> 32:59.017
Why'd you quit football?

32:59.118 --> 33:00.117
What?

33:00.220 --> 33:02.620
Was it 'cause you broke your arm?

33:04.157 --> 33:07.792
No, I just stopped
playing during college.

33:07.894 --> 33:08.793
Why?

33:09.908 --> 33:11.796
I liked other things better, I guess.

33:11.898 --> 33:13.371
Like what?

33:16.903 --> 33:18.336
Dude.

33:20.473 --> 33:23.617
I'm not the same person
I was 10 years ago, okay?

33:23.719 --> 33:24.570
Neither am I.

33:24.672 --> 33:27.417
[Chuckles] Yeah, but
you got a good excuse.

33:30.650 --> 33:32.650
So do you.

33:32.752 --> 33:35.953
♪

33:41.261 --> 33:43.160
[Indistinct conversations]

33:43.262 --> 33:45.395
[Telephone rings]

33:49.168 --> 33:51.068
You smell like a distillery.

33:51.170 --> 33:52.370
Thanks.

33:53.339 --> 33:54.238
What do you got?

33:54.340 --> 33:56.741
The older brother's got doubts.

33:56.843 --> 33:58.276
What does that mean?

33:58.378 --> 34:03.681
He's not totally sure Adam is... Adam.

34:03.750 --> 34:06.017
How the hell did you get that?

34:06.085 --> 34:07.251
[Rock music playing]

34:07.353 --> 34:08.518
[Moans]

34:08.621 --> 34:10.621
[Music continues]

34:10.723 --> 34:12.523
♪ Come on, baby, now ♪

34:12.625 --> 34:14.358
♪ Come on, baby, now ♪

34:15.146 --> 34:16.362
The brother.

34:16.466 --> 34:17.628
That's your angle.

34:17.697 --> 34:21.431
Cain and Abel, prodigal
son, it's a classic.

34:21.567 --> 34:25.335
♪

34:29.242 --> 34:32.677
Danny: <i>I'm not the same
person I was 10 years ago.</i>

34:33.880 --> 34:36.181
♪

34:36.283 --> 34:38.049
Adam: Why'd you quit football?

34:38.150 --> 34:40.051
Was it because you broke your arm?

34:40.152 --> 34:44.121
♪

34:48.795 --> 34:51.062
You got the taillight fixed, Danny.

34:51.164 --> 34:56.167
♪

34:56.268 --> 34:57.368
I wore these.

34:57.470 --> 35:00.638
I wore ones just like
these when he took me.

35:00.707 --> 35:03.908
♪

35:08.448 --> 35:11.415
I'm not the same person
I was 10 years ago.

35:11.517 --> 35:14.452
Neither am I.

35:16.994 --> 35:17.855
Mr. Warren.

35:17.958 --> 35:21.145
- Hey!
- Hey.

35:21.385 --> 35:22.284
Yeah.

35:22.386 --> 35:24.119
Do you have an appointment, hon?

35:24.221 --> 35:25.220
No.

35:25.322 --> 35:27.219
Um, look, this is a little weird,

35:27.321 --> 35:29.357
but my little brother
used to be a patient here

35:29.459 --> 35:30.992
when he was a little kid.

35:31.897 --> 35:33.629
Adam Warren.

35:33.730 --> 35:35.063
[Gasps]

35:35.165 --> 35:37.090
Oh, gosh.

35:38.210 --> 35:40.038
I've been praying for your family.

35:40.103 --> 35:41.002
Oh, cool.

35:41.104 --> 35:42.971
Cool, yeah. Thanks.

35:43.073 --> 35:45.576
Anyway, um, it's a little stupid,

35:45.678 --> 35:48.190
but we're putting together,
like, a scrapbook for him,

35:48.292 --> 35:49.311
you know, 'cause he's been gone so long,

35:49.413 --> 35:51.813
and we thought it might
be nice to have his...

35:51.915 --> 35:54.015
dental records to see.

35:54.117 --> 35:55.150
Oh, sure.

35:55.252 --> 35:55.881
[Chuckles]

35:55.983 --> 35:58.119
Just to compare. Contrast.

35:58.221 --> 36:00.188
[Keyboard clacking]

36:02.926 --> 36:05.460
Um... Ah.

36:05.562 --> 36:07.762
Your sister already picked them up.

36:09.299 --> 36:12.122
Oh. Great.

36:12.163 --> 36:13.464
[Chuckles]

36:13.877 --> 36:17.236
Thanks. Have a good day.

36:18.269 --> 36:23.573
♪

36:30.014 --> 36:31.807
So, what's the new book about?

36:31.898 --> 36:33.197
[Chuckles]

36:34.440 --> 36:36.261
Oh, hell if I know.

36:36.286 --> 36:37.220
I got my kid back.

36:37.313 --> 36:38.818
There goes my street cred
with the grief groups.

36:38.920 --> 36:39.535
[Chuckles]

36:39.560 --> 36:41.882
Tragedy fangirls will be up in arms.

36:41.984 --> 36:44.218
[Laughs] Nice being home, huh?

36:44.320 --> 36:45.586
All of us together.

36:45.688 --> 36:48.637
We'll be together a lot
more now with the campaign.

36:48.739 --> 36:50.858
Oh, no, honey. No.

36:50.960 --> 36:51.943
I only need you for a few things.

36:52.045 --> 36:53.697
No, I don't want a part in this.

36:53.799 --> 36:55.462
Photo ops and appearances.

36:55.531 --> 36:57.257
We don't need the
scrutiny right now, okay?

36:57.359 --> 36:59.687
We don't need the press
going through our trash.

36:59.789 --> 37:01.835
You worried about what they'll find?

37:04.673 --> 37:06.173
Don't be. [Chuckles]

37:06.275 --> 37:07.541
I've got you covered.

37:07.643 --> 37:09.019
What does that mean?

37:12.681 --> 37:13.685
[Chuckles]

37:13.787 --> 37:17.784
You know, the first time I saw
the name Nina on your phone,

37:17.853 --> 37:20.187
I didn't even know who she was.

37:20.289 --> 37:21.788
I was 13.

37:21.891 --> 37:23.850
I only knew Officer Meyer.

37:28.831 --> 37:33.100
Then I started erasing your
e-mails to her from your history

37:33.202 --> 37:34.968
because I knew you didn't
know how to do that,

37:35.037 --> 37:36.637
